<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        {{>head}}
    </head>
    <body>
        {{>nav}}
        <div class="main-container">
            

            <section style="margin-bottom: -6em;">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row v-align-children">
                    <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 col-sm-7 col-sm-offset-1 v-align-transform right" style="margin-top:15em;">
                        <h1 class="large mb40 mb-xs-16">PubSavvySwipe</h1>
                        <h6 class="uppercase mb16">Brought to you by Frame Research</h6>
                        <p class="lead mb40">
                            Frame Research brings you two apps for powerful medical search: PubSavvy PubMed Search and PubSavvy Swipe. These apps, featured right, enable a new way to discover medical journals. PubSavvy Swipe, our newest addition to the PubSavvy family, features a revised elegant interface for reading through and discovering medical journals.
                        </p>
                        <img style="width: 50%; height: 50%" src="site/img/download.png"/>
                    </div>
                        <div class="col-md-7 col-md-offset-1 col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-1 text-center">
                            <img style="margin-top:-12em;"class="" alt="Screenshot" src="site/img/clementine_side_edit.png" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--end of row-->
                </div>
                <!--end of container-->
            </section>

            <section class="image-square left bg-secondary" style="border-top:1px solid #ddd;border-bottom:1px solid #ddd">
                <div class="col-md-6 image">
                    <div class="background-image-holder">
                        <img alt="image" class="background-image" src="site/img/account-background-3.png" />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-1 content">
                    <h3>SEARCH SMARTER, NOT HARDER.</h3>
                    <p class="mb0">
                        Search thousands of biomedical journals at the same time, using PubSavvy's useful interface and the power of the National Library of Medicine's PubMed database. PubSavvy PubMed Search lets you access over 23 million journal abstracts indexed in PubMed/MEDLINE, using integrated tools and smart shortcuts developed by an expert searcher. Read about how PubSavvy's features help you screen through this wealth of information quickly and effectively.

                        Version 3.1 now available for iPad, iPhone, and iPodTouch. If you have multiple devices, turn on iCloud support to sync your search history and article collections across devices.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                            <h4 class="uppercase mb16">POWERED BY PUBSAVVY</h4>
                            <p class="lead mb64">
                                PubSavvy Apps give you powerful search tools at your fingertips. Our apps seamlessly integrate medical journals into a single location for discovery.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--end of row-->
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-3">
                            <div class="feature feature-1 boxed">
                                <div class="text-center">
                                    <i class="ti-panel icon"></i>
                                    <h5 class="uppercase">RUN A NEW SEARCH</h5>
                                </div>
                                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                                    PubSavvy is the only PubMed search app to offer a custom keyboard interface, so that commonly used entries are not buried 2 or 3 screens down on your iPhone standard keyboard. Simply type a commonly used term and populate the screen.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <!--end of feature-->
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm-3">
                            <div class="feature feature-1 boxed">
                                <div class="text-center">
                                    <i class="ti-panel icon"></i>
                                    <h5 class="uppercase">SEARCH HISTORY</h5>
                                </div>
                                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                                    PubSavvy saves your search history, even when you are not connected to the internet. Unlike search histories on the PubMed website which can expire after a few hours, PubSavvy search terms are stored on your device.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <!--end of feature-->
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm-3">
                            <div class="feature feature-1 boxed">
                                <div class="text-center">
                                    <i class="ti-package icon"></i>
                                    <h5 class="uppercase">REFINE SEARCH</h5>
                                </div>
                                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                                    Because the database is so comprehensive, PubMed searches often return many more citations than the user intended. PubSavvy helps you to refine your search with pre-set limits. <br> <br>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <!--end of feature-->
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm-3">
                            <div class="feature feature-1 boxed">
                                <div class="text-center">
                                    <i class="ti-pulse icon"></i>
                                    <h5 class="uppercase">VIEW FULL TEXT</h5>
                                </div>
                                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                                    PubSavvy allows you to view and email full text PDFs for open access journals and those with subscriptions held by your institution. If an article is not available yet, we'll redirect you to the PubMed page. <br><br>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <!--end of feature-->
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--end of row-->
                </div>
                <!--end of container-->
            </section>
{{>footer}}
        </div>
        {{>scripts}}
    </body>
</html>